  "_comment": "Composite indexes for cursor-paginated queries. Deploy with `firebase deploy --only firestore:indexes`. Every paginated query orders by (createdAt desc) with the document id (__name__) as a tiebreaker; Firestore sorts __name__ implicitly in the SAME direction as the last field, so createdAt-desc + __name__-desc is the default and needs NO index when there is no filter (the automatic single-field index covers it). Therefore only queries that ALSO filter need a composite index — and __name__ is omitted (it is implicit). These cover the common single- and supervisor-scoped filters; rarer multi-filter combos surface a console link with the exact definition on first run — add them here.",
